# üöÄ feature request

### Relevant Package
This feature request is for @angular/service-worker


### Description

I expect the service worker package to allow for the following behavior:
- When online, serve the server-side rendered pages for maximum first paint speed (then the client side takes over)

- When offline, fallback to the cached `index.html` in order to use the cached client app

The problem is that `ngsw-worker.js` and its configuration file `ngsw-config.json` doesn't provide a high enough granularity level to achieve that.


### Describe the solution you'd like
Change the `navigationUrls `configuration section to a `navigationUrlGroups` section similarly to `assetGroups `and `dataGroups`. This configuration section would allow to define multiple URL groups and their associated behavior, especially a boolean (could be named `enableCaching`) that would allow to set whether the URL group should be served by the server or redirected to `index.html`.
When `enableCaching` set to `true`,  the behavior would be: serve the page from the server, and fallback to `index.html` if not possible for any reason.


### Describe alternatives you've considered
I don't have any alternative solution or workaround in mind. My attempt to get the desired behavior led me to try this configuration:

    {
      "index": "/index.html",
      "assetGroups": [
        {
          "name": "app",
          "installMode": "prefetch",
          "resources": {
            "files": [
              "/favicon.ico",
              "/index.html",
              "/*.css",
              "/*.js"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "assets",
          "installMode": "lazy",
          "updateMode": "prefetch",
          "resources": {
            "files": [
              "/assets/**",
              "/*.(eot|svg|cur|jpg|png|webp|gif|otf|ttf|woff|woff2|ani)"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "dataGroups": [
        {
          "name": "backend",
          "urls": [
            "/backend/**"
          ],
          "cacheConfig": {
            "maxSize": 100,
            "maxAge": "3d",
            "strategy": "freshness"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "serverSideRenderedPages",
          "urls": [
            "/**"
          ],
          "cacheConfig": {
            "maxSize": 100,
            "maxAge": "3d",
            "strategy": "freshness"
          }
        }
      ],
      "navigationUrls": [
        "!/**"
      ]
    }

It provides a behavior close to the one I seek to achieve, but when I refresh the app in offline mode, it works only when the page has been refreshed (thus cached) in online mode before.

